    "body": "### Problem\n\nAfter https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/33048 the spellfile does not seem to be loaded before something is added (with `zg`). I think there is another part in the code where the (default) spellfile is loaded if it exists. This probably doesn't check the new path. I can investigate this later and create a PR for it, but unsure of the timeline.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. `NVIM_APPNAME=nvim-spell nvim --clean -u NONE -c 'set spell'`\n2. Insert `Nvim` (which is marked as a bad word üòù)\n3. `zg` (this should create `stdpath('data')/spell/en.utf-8.add`\n4. Quit Nvim\n5. Repeat step 1\n6. Insert Nvim\n7. Marked as bad word \n\n### Expected behavior\n\nDefault spellfile should be loaded if it exists in order to recognize 'my' recognized words\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev-84+g98f5aa2564-Homebrew\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\n-\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nMacOS 14.7.4\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nGhostty 1.1.3 with tmux 3.5a\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\ntmux-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nHomebrew",
