            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "`spell_load_lang` tries to search spell files using `do_in_runtimepath`.\n`do_in_runtimepath` searches files in `runtimepath`.\n\nAs the doc says, `runtimepath` only contains these paths,\n```\n'runtimepath' 'rtp'\tstring\t(default \"$XDG_CONFIG_HOME/nvim,\n                                               $XDG_CONFIG_DIRS[1]/nvim,\n                                               $XDG_CONFIG_DIRS[2]/nvim,\n                                               ‚Ä¶\n                                               $XDG_DATA_HOME/nvim[-data]/site,\n                                               $XDG_DATA_DIRS[1]/nvim/site,\n                                               $XDG_DATA_DIRS[2]/nvim/site,\n                                               ‚Ä¶\n                                               $VIMRUNTIME,\n                                               ‚Ä¶\n                                               $XDG_DATA_DIRS[2]/nvim/site/after,\n                                               $XDG_DATA_DIRS[1]/nvim/site/after,\n                                               $XDG_DATA_HOME/nvim[-data]/site/after,\n                                               ‚Ä¶\n                                               $XDG_CONFIG_DIRS[2]/nvim/after,\n                                               $XDG_CONFIG_DIRS[1]/nvim/after,\n                                               $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/nvim/after\")\n```\n\nBut the additional spell files created by `zg` are under `$XDG_DATA_HOME/spell`.\nAs the `$XDG_DATA_HOME` isn't in `runtimepath`, the spell files won't be found.\n\nAnd during searching, the `runtime_search_path_get_cached` only returns several paths,\n```\nruntime\nruntime/pack/dist/opt/netrw\nruntime/pack/dist/opt/matchit\nbuild/lib/nvim\n\n```",
